    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="439"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/599</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Danish Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Brun</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Danish Government is desirous to learn whether the United States, if England
                    applies Article 2 of the order in council of October 29, 1914,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d439fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1914Supp#pg_262">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1914, Supplement, p.
                        262</ref>.</note> to Denmark, would recognize the right of England to seize
                    American vessels carrying conditional contraband of war to ports of Denmark.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">C. Brun</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
